<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "5B">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B5206020" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "02" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Countershaft Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B5206010">Manual Transaxle Unit Dismounting and Remounting</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B5206014">Fifth Gear Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B5206015">Manual Transaxle Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B5206018">Input Shaft and Countershaft Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B5206020001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove left bearing cone (2) with 4th gear (3) using puller (4) and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
To avoid gear teeth damage, support 4th gear (3) on flat side of puller.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520054.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.237mm" ver = "01" gw = "151" gh = "103"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "3.150in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Countershaft
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply puller (5) to 2nd gear (4), and remove 3rd &#38; 4th gear spacer (2) and 3rd gear (3) together with 2nd gear using hydraulic press. Needle bearing would come out with 2nd gear.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
To avoid gear teeth damage, be sure to support 2nd gear on flat side of bearing puller.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520055.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "47.360mm" ver = "01" gw = "149" gh = "117"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "3.150in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Countershaft
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove 2nd synchronizer outer ring, center cone and inner ring.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using snap ring pliers (3), remove circlip (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7RW01520008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.645mm" ver = "01" gw = "137" gh = "124"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "3.150in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Low speed synchronizer sleeve
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply puller (3) to 1st gear (2) and remove low speed synchronizer sleeve &#38; hub assembly (1) with 1st gear using hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
To avoid gear teeth damage, support 1st gear on flat side of bearing puller.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520057.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "41.094mm" ver = "01" gw = "142" gh = "99"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disassemble synchronizer sleeve &#38; hub assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove 1st gear needle bearing from shaft.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
In order to remove right bearing (1) from countershaft, grind with a grinder (2) one part “a” of right bearing (1) as illustrated till it becomes thin.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Be careful not to grind countershaft (3).
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0A520035.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "48.939mm" ver = "01" gw = "164" gh = "122"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Break right bearing (2) at thin point with a chisel (1) to remove it.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0A520036.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "43.523mm" ver = "01" gw = "151" gh = "107"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<c-change/>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B5206020002">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean all components thoroughly, inspect them for any abnormality and replace with new one if necessary.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check the following:
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Clearance between synchronizer ring (2) and gear (1)
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Clearance “a” between synchronizer ring and gear
</title>
<ptxt>
Standard: 1.0 – 1.4 mm (0.040 – 0.055 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 0.5 mm (0.020 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
</item>
</list1>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Key slot width
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Key slot width “b”
</title>
<ptxt>
Standard: 10.0 – 10.2 mm (0.394 – 0.401 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 10.45 mm (0.4114 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
</item>
</list1>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5JB0A520079.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "79.321mm" ver = "01" gw = "136" gh = "208"/>
</figure>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Each chamfered tooth of gear and synchronizer ring for abnormal wear and damage
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Gear tooth for abnormal wear and damage
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<ptxt>
Replace it with new one if necessary.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check the following:
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Difference between outer ring (1) and inner ring (3).
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Difference between synchronizer outer ring and inner ring (2nd) “a”
</title>
<ptxt>
Standard: 0.95 – 1.25 mm (0.0375 – 0.0492 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 0.5 mm (0.0196 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
</item>
</list1>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A520028.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "48.884mm" ver = "01" gw = "50" gh = "122"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.968in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
2.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Center cone
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Each chamfered tooth of gear and synchronizer ring for abnormal wear and damage
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Gear tooth for abnormal wear and damage
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<ptxt>
Replace it with new one if necessary.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
To ensure lubrication of countershaft (1), blow air into oil holes (2) as shown in figure and make sure that they are free from any obstruction.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520060.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "35.168mm" ver = "01" gw = "190" gh = "83"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Fit low speed synchronizer sleeve (4) to hub (3), insert 3 keys (2) in it and then set springs (1) at specified position as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Be sure to assemble sleeve and hub in correct direction. (No direction is specified to each key.)
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Low speed synchronizer keys and springs are larger than high speed ones in size.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<spec>
<title>
Synchronizer key installation position
</title>
<ptxt>
“a” = “b”
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A520029.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "67.722mm" ver = "01" gw = "184" gh = "175"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "3.150in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[a]: 
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
1st gear side
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install right bearing cone (1) to countershaft (2) using special tools and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B023">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-76010">
09913–76010
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B024">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09924-74530">
09924–74530
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I5RW0A520038.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.803mm" ver = "01" gw = "82" gh = "125"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install needle bearing (4), apply oil to it, then install 1st gear (3).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install synchronizer outer ring (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install low speed sleeve &#38; hub assembly (1) using special tools and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Support shaft with special tool as shown in figure so that retainer of bearing cone will be free from compression.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Make sure that synchronizer ring key slots (8) are aligned with keys (5) while press-fitting sleeve &#38; hub assembly.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Check free rotation of 1st gear (3) after press-fitting sleeve &#38; hub assembly.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B025">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09922-76340">
09922–76340
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B026">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-85210">
09913–85210
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B027">
<s-part>
(C)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09940-54910">
09940–54910
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B028">
<s-part>
(D)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09924-07710">
09924–07710
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A520030.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "86.010mm" ver = "01" gw = "165" gh = "227"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.318in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.318in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[a]: 
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
1st gear side
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[b]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Short flange
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new circlip (1) to groove securely.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install needle bearing (2) and apply oil to needle bearing.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Install 2nd gear (6) with synchronizer outer ring (3), center cone (4) and inner ring (5) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A520031.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "74.834mm" ver = "01" gw = "169" gh = "195"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "3.150in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[A]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Section [a] – [a]
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Press-fit 3rd gear (2) and spacer (1) using special tools and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
It is recommended to press-fit spacer and 3rd gear first, and then 4th gear later separately so that countershaft will not be compressed excessively.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B029">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09922-76340">
09922–76340
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B030">
<s-part>
(B)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-85210">
09913–85210
</s-number>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RH01520036.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.053mm" ver = "01" gw = "85" gh = "122"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.315in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "3.150in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
3.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
2nd gear
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Press-fit 4th gear (2) using the same procedure as step 11).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install left bearing cone (1) using special tool and hydraulic press.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
For protection of bearing cone (3), be sure to support shaft with special tool as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B031">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09922-76340">
09922–76340
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B032">
<s-part>
(E)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09913-80113">
09913–80113
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520066.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.476mm" ver = "01" gw = "76" gh = "123"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
